    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Three-Hour Poll Tax'' (editorial, ''Making Votes Count'' series, Oct. 27), about the waiting-in-line penalty:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Three-Hour Poll Tax'' (editorial, ''Making Votes Count'' series, Oct. 27), about the waiting-in-line penalty:</p>
        <p>Clearly it is time we adopt the European system of weekend voting. This not only allows those often disenfranchised a better opportunity to vote, but also permits ''staggered'' and more leisure-time voting over the two days.</p>
        <p>And with voters less stressed, turnout would surely increase.</p>
        <p>James Huff  Chapel Hill, N.C.  Oct. 27, 2004</p>
      </block>
